<div class="xar-mod-head"><span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>Administration - Categories</xar:mlstring></span></div>
<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
    <div style="padding: 1px;" class="xar-norm-outline">
        <div style="float:right;padding:10px;">
            <img src="modules/adminpanels/xarimages/admin.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
        </div>
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <em><xar:mlstring>Categories is a Xaraya Utility Module.</xar:mlstring></em>
            <xar:mlstring>It is currently responsible for accomplishing these tasks:</xar:mlstring>
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Allows the use of site wide categories for content modules to use as needed.</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>From the menu, you have two choices.  'Add a New Category', and 'View Categories'.</xar:mlstring>
            <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Add a new category -- Allows you to add a new category to your site categories tree.</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>View Categories -- This area allows you to view the entire categorization tree, allowing a easy way to modify it.</xar:mlstring></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>The Navigation block allows navigation of any module using the category hooks.</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>Categories provides all the hooks necessary to allow categories to be available within other modules.</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
